President Biden spoke with the governors of Arkansas, Illinois, Kentucky, Missouri, and Tennessee to express his condolences for the lives lost and the damage caused by the recent tornadoes and extreme weather. He asked each governor what their state needs and how he can best support them. The president assured them of his commitment to delivering assistance quickly through FEMA. He also urged the governors to reach out to him directly if they require any federal support and stated that he will remain focused on helping communities recover from the effects of the storm. The president was accompanied on the call by FEMA Administrator Deanne Criswell, Homeland Security Advisor Liz Sherwood-Randall, Deputy Chief of Staff Jen O'Malley Dillon, and White House Director of Intergovernmental Affairs Julie Chavez Rodriguez.